Client Scripts (ServiceNow)
🔹 What are Client Scripts?

Client Scripts are scripts that run on the client side (browser) to control form behavior and improve user interaction without reloading the page.

🔹 Features
Execute in the user's browser
Validate user input
Modify field behavior dynamically
Improve form responsiveness
Reduce unnecessary server calls
🔹 Types of Client Scripts
1. onLoad()

Runs when the form loads.

Use Cases:

Set default values
Hide fields initially
Display messages

Example:
Show a welcome message when the form opens.

2. onChange()

Runs when a field value changes.

Use Cases:

Validate field input
Auto-populate fields
Show/hide fields dynamically

Example:
If Priority = High, display additional fields.

3. onSubmit()

Runs when the user submits the form.

Use Cases:

Validate mandatory fields
Prevent incorrect submission

Example:
Block form submission if required data is missing.

4. onCellEdit()

Runs when editing fields directly in a list.

Use Cases:

Validate list updates
Control inline editing
🔹 Common Objects Used
g_form → Manipulates form fields
g_user → Access current user details
g_scratchpad → Pass server data to client
🔹 Example

Scenario:
If State = Closed, make Close Notes mandatory.

function onChange(control, oldValue, newValue, isLoading) {
if(newValue == 'Closed'){
g_form.setMandatory('close_notes', true);
}
}
🔹 Benefits
Better user experience
Faster validation
Reduces server processing
Dynamic form behavior
